# LittleFS data directory

This directory is the source for the LittleFS filesystem image built for the
ESP32-S3 head unit (`board_build.filesystem = littlefs` in platformio.ini).

It is intentionally (almost) empty: the firmware does NOT ship any files in the
image. `Config` writes its settings blob to LittleFS at runtime, and on first
boot after the blob layout changes it resets to defaults. The build only needs
this directory to EXIST so `mklittlefs` can build a valid (empty) image.

This `.gitkeep` exists so the directory survives fresh checkouts — git does not
track empty directories, and a missing `data/` causes:
    warning: can't read source directory
    *** [.pio\...\littlefs.bin] Error 1

Do not delete this file unless you add other content to this directory.
